Wendover informs his readers in his text the years in which Marianus Scotus and Sigehert of Gemblours ended their histories3 hut such statements, we know, cannot imply that all before those respective years was by their hand. And so in the present instance, if the writer of the Introduction will turn to Pits, edit. 1619, p. 255, he will there read that John of Hagus· taldt, or Hexham, continued his chronicle to the first year of the reign of king Richard the first, namely, 1189, a date which exactly tallies with the marginal note. This is not offered as the solution of the difficulty, although it would appear to be a very simple and natural one.
